news.title: New ready reckoner rates in Maharashtra unlikely before Lok Sabha polls
news.para: A source in the govt on Wednesday said the state would consider the LS polls and the of the real estate market sentiment before deciding on the rates. “The elections are likely to affect the announcement of the RR rates.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government cancels land acquisition notification in Amaravati
news.para: The previous TDP govt had pooled up about 34,000 acres of land from farmers in 29 villages which were earmarked as capital city area through the land pooling scheme (LPS).

news.title: ICICI Prudential Life leases 2.52 lakh sq ft office space in Mumbai
news.para: The insurance major has leased this office space - spread across four floors - for five years through a structured deal, a person cited earlier said, adding that the company will be paying a monthly rental of 91.5 per sq ft for the office space.

news.title: Haryana: 20 illegal colonies razed, DTCP urges cops for FIRs
news.para: “These illegal colonies were developed in Gurgaon, Sohna, Pataudi and Farrukhnagar in the past few months,” an official said.

news.title: NCLT-appointed committee asks JAL to hand over nine projects in Jaypee Wish Town
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT)-appointed implementation and monitoring committee (IMC) wrote to JIL’s holding company Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) earlier this week, seeking possession of towers at these nine projects immediately.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to establish town and country planning directorate
news.para: Under the plan, a town and country planning directorate will be set up, which will govern the development not only within the housing development authorities but also within urban local bodies.

news.title: Mumbai: No possession for three years, buyers protest against Bhagwati Developers
news.para: The Bhagwati Greens-III housing project next to ISKCON temple has three wings with 135 flats and 25 shops. Both A & B wings have 28 floors with 44 and 66 flats, respectively, while the C wing has 25 floors with 25 flats and 25 shops.

news.title: Delhi development body opens booking for 10,000 ready flats
news.para: Delhi Development Authority offers diverse flats in Narela under Diwali Special Housing Scheme 2023 Phase III. MIG flats in Sector A1-A4 are also available. Jasola, Rohini, Loknayak Puram feature varied affordable housing options.

news.title: US: Lennar Corp posts revenue of $7.33 billion in quarter ended February 2024
news.para: "Macroeconomic environment remained relatively consistent throughout the quarter," said Stuart Miller, Lennar's co-CEO, and added that housing supply remained chronically short due to production deficits over a decade.

news.title: US lawmakers to propose legislation seeking scrutiny of Chinese real estate purchases
news.para: Representative Elissa Slotkin, a Democrat, and Republican Blake Moore are proposing to expand the authority of the Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States (CFIUS) over foreign real estate purchases.

news.title: Britain's Vistry posts pre-tax profit of 419.1 million pounds in 2023
news.para: Britain's house building market has seen some signs of stability, partly driven by an easing in borrowing costs at the start of this year, after high inflation and rising interest rates crimped demand in 2023.

news.title: Austria: Creditors could recover 32% of debt in Signa Prime restructuring plan
news.para: The calculation is based on a new plan, which creditors must vote on in a meeting scheduled for next Monday, and which foresees a trustee taking over the sale of Signa Prime's assets.

news.title: Germany is halfway through property crisis: Henning Koch, chief executive, Commerzbank
news.para: The euro zone's largest economy is in the grip of its worst property slump since at least the 2007-9 global financial crisis, after a sharp rise in borrowing costs and a higher proportion of riskier lending tipped the sector into one of Europe's biggest downturns.

news.title: Thailand's Italian-Thai Development flags cash flow issues, seeks bank loans
news.para: Italian-Thai Development told the Stock Exchange of Thailand that revenue from construction projects remained smaller than its overall expenses.

news.title: Savills profit before tax dips 42% to $121.32 million in 2023
news.para: Transaction activity in the global property markets has remained weak since the onset of the pandemic, particularly in the office and retail segments, while elevated interest levels and tighter credit conditions have further punctured deal appetite.

news.title: Telangana: CCLA issues notices to five companies in illegal land encroachment
news.para: The Board directed My Home Industries and others to appear before the secretary of Bhoodan Yagna Board at Chief Commissioner of Land Administration (CCLA) office on March 16 for a hearing with documents or proof, if any, in support of their claim.

news.title: Madras HC issues notice to state government over encroachment in Kodaikanal
news.para: A division bench of Justice D Krishnakumar and Justice R Vijayakumar sought a report from the state while hearing a public interest litigation filed by R Johar of Dindigul.

news.title: 360 ONE- backed NeoLiv raises Rs 300 crore as first close of its AIF
news.para: NeoLiv raises Rs 300 crore for Inliv Real Estate Fund, targeting MMR, NCR, tier 2 cities. CEO Malhotra plans quick deployment. Strong interest from investors like family offices, UHNIs, CXOs noted.

news.title: Panic purchase of sand triggers price rise in NTR district
news.para: Summer happens to be the peak season for construction industry. There is enough availability of sand and other raw materials required for construction works during this season.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh CM launches auto-DCR system for approval of building plans
news.para: Another feature of the system is that the registered architect can permit and approve the construction of residential accommodation in an area of up to 500 square feet.
